14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 34-109 of Title 11, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. A municipal police officer who retires under the Oklahoma
19 Police Pension and Retirement System pursuant to Sections 50-101
20 through 50-136.8 of Title 11 of the Oklahoma Statutes may request to
21 retain custody and possession of his or her municipal-issued firearm
22 and badge. The retiring officer shall request in writing to the
23 head of the municipal law enforcement agency of the municipality in
24 which the officer is retiring for permission to retain custody and
